    "creation_date" : 1291981954,
    "answer_id" : 4408561,
    "question_id" : 1196586,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 2.5",
    "body" : "<p>Yes you can use the for-each loop,\nTo do that you have to maintain a separate list to hold removing items and then remove that list from names list using <code>removeAll()</code> method,</p>\n\n<pre><code>List&lt;String&gt; names = ....\n\n// introduce a separate list to hold removing items\nList&lt;String&gt; toRemove= new ArrayList&lt;String&gt;();\n\nfor (String name : names) {\n   // Do something: perform conditional checks\n   toRemove.add(name);\n}    \nnames.removeAll(toRemove);\n\n// now names list holds expected values\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 691469,
      "reputation" : 19,
      "user_id" : 564051,
      "user_type" : "unregistered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/53a160b1cddc9418c7faf5963f398180?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
