      },
      "edited" : false,
      "score" : 2,
      "creation_date" : 1486176325,
      "post_id" : 6046087,
      "comment_id" : 71246150,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "Such indexed based operations should only be conducted on lists whose elements can be accessed in O(1) constant time. If the list is not randomly accessible (does not implement RandomAccess) then you should use an iterator instead, as these types of collections usually take longer to retrieve an element at a specific index position, such as a LinkedList."
    }, {
